<body>
  <div id=3D"container">
    <div id=3D"header">
      <p>
	<i>Linear Algebra</i>
      </p>
    </div>
    <div id=3D"content">
      <div id=3D"innercontent">
	<img id=3D"cover" src=3D"https://hefferon.net/linearalgebra/cover.png" alt=
=3D"cover of Linear Algebra by Hefferon">
	<p>
	  <i>Linear Algebra</i>
	  by Jim Hefferon=20
	  is a text for a first undergraduate course.
	  It is Free.
	  Use it as the main book, as a supplement, or for independent study.
	</p>

	<h3 id=3D"get_the_book">
	  Get the book
	</h3>
        <p>
	  Clicking on this link offers you a chance to contribute to
	  OpenIntro,
	  who work to make Open materials more adoptable.
	  You can get the electronic version of the
	  text for free by just setting the slider to 0:
	  <a href=3D"https://www.openintro.org/go?id=3Dlinalg4&amp;referrer=3Dheff=
eron.net">Download <i>Linear Algebra</i></a>.
	  (If you do contribute to
	  <a href=3D"https://www.openintro.org/">OpenIntro.org</a>
          then note that the page wording is confusing.
	  It says that the money
	  goes to the author but instead it means OpenIntro.)
	</p>

	<h3>
	  Text highlights
	</h3>
=09
	<ul class=3D"nobullet">
	  <li><span class=3D"listitem">Standard coverage</span>
            Linear systems and Gauss's method,=20
	    vector spaces, linear maps and matrices, determinants,
	    and eigenvectors and eigenvalues.
          </li>
	 =20
	  <li><span class=3D"listitem">Developmental approach</span>
	    The book proves all of the results
	    but does not start by assuming that=20
	    students are already able at abstract work.
	    Instead, it proceeds with a great deal of
	    motivation, many computational examples,=20
            and many exercises.
	    The goal is to raise=20
            each student's level of=20
	    mathematical maturity.
          </li>
	 =20
	  <li><span class=3D"listitem">Extensive exercise sets</span>  =20
            Each subsection has a wide range of exercises,
            from=20
	    routine verifications to a few challenges.
	    The
	    <a href=3D"https://jheffero.w3.uvm.edu/linearalgebra/jhanswer.pdf">boo=
k of solutions</a>
	    gives the answer to every one, completely worked.
	    And, clicking on a problem=20
	    takes you to its answer
	    while clicking on the answer takes you back to the problem.
          </li>
	 =20
	  <li><span class=3D"listitem">Popular</span>
	    Used in hundreds of classes at many schools,=20
            as well as by thousands of people
            for independent study.
          </li>
	 =20
	  <li><span class=3D"listitem">Applications</span>
            Each chapter finishes with four or five short =20
	    supplemental topics
            for reading or projects, or for
            small group work.=20
          </li>=20
	 =20
	  <li><span class=3D"listitem">Extras</span>
            There are
	    <a href=3D"https://jheffero.w3.uvm.edu/linearalgebra/slides.zip">beame=
r slides</a>
	    for classroom presentations,=20
            a
	    <a href=3D"https://jheffero.w3.uvm.edu/linearalgebra/lab.pdf">lab manu=
al</a>=20
	    using
	    <a href=3D"https://www.sagemath.org/"><i>Sage</i></a>,
	    and <a href=3D"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=3DPLwF3A0R8OzMoMl=
E1-SaEh8h9VqUlO-r52">videos</a>.
	    For more, see the page for <a href=3D"https://hefferon.net/linearalgeb=
ra/teaching.html">instructors</a>.
          </li>=20
	 =20
	  <li><span class=3D"listitem">Prerequisite</span>
            One semester of calculus.
          </li>
	 =20
	  <li><span class=3D"listitem">Free</span>
            Everything is=20
	    <a href=3D"https://hefferon.net/source.html">Freely available</a>,
	    including the
	    <a href=3D"https://gitlab.com/jim.hefferon/linear-algebra"><span class=
=3D"latex">L<sup>a</sup>T<sub>e</sub>X</span> source</a>.
	    You can also buy a
	    <a href=3D"https://hefferon.net/linearalgebra/hardcopy.html">paper cop=
y of the book</a>.
          </li>
	 =20
	  <li><span class=3D"listitem">Reviews</span>
            Some from:
            <a href=3D"https://mathdl.maa.org/mathDL/19/?pa=3Dreviews&amp;s=
a=3DviewBook&amp;bookId=3D72055">the Mathematical Association of America</a=
>,
            <a href=3D"https://open.umn.edu/opentextbooks/textbooks/24">the=
 American Institute of Mathematics</a>,
            <a href=3D"https://open.umn.edu/opentextbooks/BookDetail.aspx?b=
ookId=3D24">the Open Textbook Library</a>,
            <a href=3D"https://www.theassayer.org/cgi-bin/asbook.cgi?book=
=3D29"><i>The Assayer</i>, a longstanding site about free texts</a>.
          </li>
	 =20
	  <li><span class=3D"listitem">Award winning</span>
            Recipient of the 2020 Solow Award
	    from the Mathematical Association of America, for
	    =E2=80=9Cimpact on undergraduate education in mathematics.=E2=80=9D
          </li>
	</ul>
      </div>

      </div>
    </div>
